This paper focuses on energy-efficient wireless communication, which is a key research area in the field of networked systems and communication. The paper specifically investigates inter-network cooperation, which involves multiple network access interfaces, and analyzes the energy consumption of different schemes. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also considers physical-layer channel impairments and upper-layer protocol overheads, which are key topics in information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper proposes a cooperative scheme that involves multiple users, which can be considered a system-level approach and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of network cooperation, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
